				<h4 id="syntax">
					Syntax
				</h4>
				<p>
					The syntax for <mono>paginate</mono> calls is:
<div align="center" style="margin-top:-15px">
<mono>f++</mono>: &nbsp; <pre class="prettyprint inline lang-nift" style="margin-bottom:-15px">
paginate
</pre>
</div><br>
<div align="center">
<mono>n++</mono>: &nbsp; <pre class="prettyprint inline lang-nift" style="margin-bottom:-15px">
\@paginate
</pre>
</div>
				</p>

				<h4 id="description">
					Description
				</h4>
				<p>
					The <mono>paginate</mono> function is for specifying with pagination where to insert pages in to the file being built, it takes zero parameters.
				</p>

				<h4 id="n++-eg">
					n++ example
				</h4>
				<p>
					Example of <mono>paginate</mono> being used with <mono>n++</mono>:					

<div align="center" style="margin-top:-10px; margin-bottom:10px">
<pre class="prettyprint inline linenums lang-nift">
\@paginate

\@paginate.no_items_per_page(2)

\@paginate.template
{
	<p>
		\@if{!s}(\$[paginate.page_no] > 1)
			<a href="\@pathtopageno(\@`\$[paginate.page_no]-1`)">previous</a> 
		\@if{!s}(\$[paginate.page_no] < \$[paginate.no_pages])
			<a href="\@pathtopageno(\@`\$[paginate.page_no]+1`)">next</a>
	</p>

	\$[paginate.page]
}

\@item
{
	<p>
		item 1
	</p>
}
\@item
{
	<p>
		item 2
	</p>
}
\@item
{
	<p>
		item 3
	</p>
}
\@item
{
	<p>
		item 4
	</p>
}</pre>
</div>
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>
</section>
